The paper deals with resource allocation in multi-carrier coordinated multi-point (CoMP) systems with limited feedback, which involves optimization of wireless communication networks. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of algorithms to achieve energy efficiency and quality-of-service, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of simulations to evaluate the performance of the proposed algorithms, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
